'''The Pisagua Case''' is the name given to the legal actions taken surrounding the crimes that occurred in the torture center and [[Pisagua Prison Camp|prison camp]] installed in the town of [[Pisagua, Chile|Pisagua]], during the [[Military government of Chile (1973<U+2013>90)|military regime]] of [[Augusto Pinochet]] in [[Chile]].

==History==
[[File:Memorial DDHH Chile - 01 Fosa de Pisagua.jpg|thumb|200 px|Fosa de Pisagua]]
The judicial investigation began prior to the claim of illegal burial presented by the [[Vicariate of Solidarity]], 31 May 1990 in the [[Pozo Almonte]] Court.<ref name="memoria">{{cite web |url=http://www.memoriayjusticia.cl/espanol/sp_enfoque-pisagua.html#hallazgo |title=El Hallazgo de la Fosa |work=Memoria Viva |accessdate=4 July 2012}}{{es icon}}</ref>

On 2 June 1990 the mass grave was found,<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.memoriayjusticia.cl/espanol/sp_docs-pisaqua-map2.html |title=Plano de la fosa com<U+00FA>n en el cementerio de Pisagua |work=Memoria Viva |accessdate=4 July 2012}}{{es icon}}</ref> located in the north-west sector of the Pisagua Cemetery. Twenty bodies were discovered within the grave, well-preserved due to the salt that permeates the sand in the area.<ref name="memoria"/>

==List of prisoners executed in Pisagua==
The majority of the executed were found in 1990 during an investigation led by Minister [[Hern<U+00E1>n S<U+00E1>nchez Marr<U+00E9>]].<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.memoriayjusticia.cl/espanol/sp_docs-pisaqua.html |title=Documentos Caso Pisagua |work=Memoria Viva |accessdate=4 July  2012}}{{es icon}}</ref>

'''Shot under the <U+201C>Escape Law<U+201D> 29 September 1973'''
* Juan Calder<U+00F3>n Villal<U+00F3>n
* Nolberto Ca<U+00F1>as Ca<U+00F1>as
* Marcelo Guzm<U+00E1>n Fuentes
* Juan Jim<U+00E9>nez Vidal
* Luis Lizardi Lizardi
* Michel Nash Sa<U+00E9>z

'''Executed by the First War Council 11 October 1973'''
* Julio Cabezas Gacit<U+00FA>a
* Jos<U+00E9> Rufino C<U+00F3>rdova Croxatto
* Humberto Lizardi Flores
* Mario Morris Barrios
* Juan Valencia Hinojoso

'''Executed by the Second War Council 29 October 1973'''
* Rodolfo Fuenzalida Fern<U+00E1>ndez
* Juan Antonio Ruz D<U+00ED>az
* Jos<U+00E9> Dem<U+00F3>stenes Sampson Ocaranza
* Freddy Marcelo Taberna Gallegos

'''Executed by the Third War Council 29 November 1973'''
* Germ<U+00E1>n Palominos Lamas

'''Executed by the Fourth War Council 11 February 1974'''
* Luis Toro Castillo
* Alberto Ya<U+00F1>ez Carvajal

'''Declared Missing ([[Desaparecidos#Chile|Desaparecidos]]) of [[Iquique]], [[Tarapac<U+00E1> Region|Region of Tarapac<U+00E1>]], Chile'''
* William Millar Sanhueza
* Jorge Mar<U+00ED>n Rossel
* Manuel Araya Zavala

'''The Executed of Iquique, Region of Tarapac<U+00E1>, Chile'''
* Luis Rojas Valenzuela (17 de septiembre de 1973)
* Oscar Ripoll Codoceo (20 de octubre de 1973)
* Julio Valenzuela Bast<U+00ED>as (20 de octubre de 1973)
* Manuel Donoso Da<U+00F1>obettia (20 de octubre de 1973)
* Gerardo Poblete Fern<U+00E1>ndez (21 de octubre de 1973)
* Luis Solar Welchs (23 de octubre de 1973)
* Isaias Higuera Zu<U+00F1>iga (11 de enero de 1974)
* Nelson M<U+00E1>rquez Agusto (18 de enero de 1974)
* Manuel Sanhueza Mellado (10 de julio de 1974)
* Henry Torres Flores

